---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import AuthorBox from '../../components/AuthorBox.astro';

const title = "UK AI Search Visibility Market Report Q2 2026 | Rank4AI";
const description = "Over 60% of UK adults now use AI-assisted search monthly. This Q2 2026 report covers adoption, platform share, and business readiness across the UK AI sear";
const faqs = [{"q": "What is the current state of AI search visibility for UK businesses in 2026?", "a": "AI-assisted search has moved from early adoption to mainstream behaviour in the UK, with Google AI Overviews alone reaching over 1 billion users globally and ChatGPT exceeding 200 million weekly active users. UK businesses face a measurable citation gap: brands without structured data, strong E-E-A-T signals, and authoritative content are largely absent from AI-generated answers. This represents a growing competitive risk for organisations that have not yet invested in AI search visibility as a discipline."}, {"q": "How does Google AI Overviews affect organic search traffic for UK websites?", "a": "Early data from Semrush and Ahrefs indicates that organic click-through rates decline when AI Overviews are displayed for a query, with some studies citing average traffic reductions of around 9% on affected pages. Approximately 70% of AI Overview citations come from sources already ranking on page one of standard Google results, meaning that existing domain authority remains a prerequisite for AI citation. UK brands investing in traditional SEO fundamentals are currently better positioned for AI citation than those that are not."}, {"q": "Which AI search platforms are most relevant to UK marketers right now?", "a": "Google AI Overviews is the highest-reach platform in the UK given Google's 92.7% UK search market share (Statcounter, Q1 2025). ChatGPT and Microsoft Copilot, both powered primarily by the Bing index, are the next most significant platforms for UK brand citation. Perplexity AI, valued at $9 billion in January 2025 and reporting 100 million monthly global users, is growing rapidly and uses a cited-answer format that rewards brands with strong web presence."}, {"q": "Are UK businesses investing adequately in AI search visibility?", "a": "Adoption of AI technologies across UK businesses is uneven. DSIT data shows that 75% of large UK businesses had adopted at least one AI technology by 2023, compared with only 15% of small businesses. Gartner's 2024 CMO Spend Survey found that 34% of UK CMOs cited AI-driven search as a top-three priority for 2025, suggesting growing awareness at senior level. However, structured investment in AI search visibility as a distinct discipline remains limited across most UK organisations."}, {"q": "What content and technical factors influence whether a UK brand is cited by AI search engines?", "a": "Semrush research indicates that structured data markup and strong E-E-A-T (Experience, Expertise, Authoritativeness, Trustworthiness) signals are associated with approximately three times the citation rate in AI Overviews compared to pages without these attributes. Ranking in the top ten organic results for a query remains the single strongest predictor of AI citation, making domain authority and topical relevance foundational requirements. Brands should also ensure their content is crawlable and that factual claims are clearly attributed."}, {"q": "How large is the commercial opportunity in UK AI search visibility?", "a": "PwC UK estimates that AI could contribute up to \u00a3900 billion to the UK economy by 2030, and UK digital advertising spend reached \u00a319.6 billion in 2023 (IAB UK). As AI-generated answers increasingly determine which brands are seen by consumers, AI search visibility is becoming a direct revenue lever rather than a peripheral marketing concern. Organisations that establish citation authority early will be positioned to capture disproportionate visibility as AI search adoption continues to grow."}];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="pt-12 pb-24">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <Breadcrumbs items={[
        { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
        { label: 'Research', href: '/research/' },
        { label: 'Market Report Q2 2026' }
      ]} />

      <p class="section-tag">Research / Market Report</p>
      <h1 class="mb-6">UK AI Search Visibility Market Report Q2 2026</h1>
      <p class="text-xs text-text-muted mb-6">By Adam Parker, Founder of Rank4AI. Published 24 April 2026. All figures sourced from named organisations cited inline.</p>

      <p class="answer-capsule text-[18px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-10">
        AI-assisted search is now a mainstream behaviour in the UK. Google AI Overviews reached over 1 billion users globally by May 2024 (Google I/O 2024). ChatGPT surpassed 200 million weekly active users globally by August 2024 (OpenAI). UK internet penetration stands at 97% (ONS 2024). UK businesses are largely unprepared for AI-driven citation, creating a measurable visibility gap for brands not actively managing their presence in large language model outputs.
      </p>

      <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Market Size and Adoption</h2><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">97%</span><p class="text-text-muted">UK internet penetration rate among adults, 2024. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/businessindustryandtrade/itandinternetindustry/bulletins/internetusers/2024" class="text-teal hover:underline">Office for National Statistics</a></span></p></div><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">200 million+</span><p class="text-text-muted">ChatGPT weekly active users globally as of August 2024. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://openai.com/blog/chatgpt-can-now-see-hear-and-speak" class="text-teal hover:underline">OpenAI</a></span></p></div><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">1 billion+</span><p class="text-text-muted">Users served by Google AI Overviews globally within one year of launch, May 2024. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://blog.google/technology/ai/google-io-2024-keynote/" class="text-teal hover:underline">Google I/O 2024 Keynote</a></span></p></div><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">58%</span><p class="text-text-muted">Share of UK adults who used the internet for finding information in the most recent ONS reporting period. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/businessindustryandtrade/itandinternetindustry/bulletins/internetusers/2024" class="text-teal hover:underline">Office for National Statistics</a></span></p></div><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">£19.6 billion</span><p class="text-text-muted">UK digital advertising market total spend in 2023. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://www.iabuk.com/research/digital-adspend" class="text-teal hover:underline">IAB UK / PricewaterhouseCoopers Digital Adspend Study 2024</a></span></p></div><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">79%</span><p class="text-text-muted">Share of UK marketing budgets allocated to digital channels in 2023. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://www.iabuk.com/research/digital-adspend" class="text-teal hover:underline">IAB UK</a></span></p></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Platform Landscape: AI Search Engines in the UK</h2><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">92.7%</span><p class="text-text-muted">Google search engine market share in the UK, Q1 2025. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://gs.statcounter.com/search-engine-market-share/all/united-kingdom" class="text-teal hover:underline">Statcounter GlobalStats</a></span></p></div><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">3.9%</span><p class="text-text-muted">Bing search engine market share in the UK, Q1 2025 (Bing powers ChatGPT Browse and Copilot web results). <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://gs.statcounter.com/search-engine-market-share/all/united-kingdom" class="text-teal hover:underline">Statcounter GlobalStats</a></span></p></div><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">100 million+</span><p class="text-text-muted">Perplexity AI monthly active users globally, reported early 2025. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://www.reuters.com/technology/artificial-intelligence/perplexity-ai-valued-9-billion-new-funding-round-2025-01-07/" class="text-teal hover:underline">Perplexity AI public disclosure via Reuters</a></span></p></div><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">$9 billion</span><p class="text-text-muted">Perplexity AI valuation as of January 2025 funding round, indicating sustained platform growth. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://www.reuters.com/technology/artificial-intelligence/perplexity-ai-valued-9-billion-new-funding-round-2025-01-07/" class="text-teal hover:underline">Reuters</a></span></p></div><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">63%</span><p class="text-text-muted">Share of Google Search results pages in the US that showed AI Overviews in tested queries by late 2024, indicating the scale of AI integration into search results. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://www.semrush.com/blog/google-ai-overviews/" class="text-teal hover:underline">Semrush Sensor / Semrush Blog</a></span></p></div><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">2.3 million</span><p class="text-text-muted">Estimated UK monthly visits to Perplexity.ai, Q4 2024. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://www.similarweb.com/website/perplexity.ai/" class="text-teal hover:underline">Similarweb</a></span></p></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">UK Business Readiness for AI Search Visibility</h2><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">75%</span><p class="text-text-muted">Share of UK large businesses that had adopted at least one AI technology by 2023. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ai-activity-in-uk-businesses" class="text-teal hover:underline">Department for Science, Innovation and Technology (DSIT) AI Adoption in UK Businesses survey 2023</a></span></p></div><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">15%</span><p class="text-text-muted">Share of UK small businesses that had adopted at least one AI technology by 2023, highlighting an SME readiness gap. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ai-activity-in-uk-businesses" class="text-teal hover:underline">Department for Science, Innovation and Technology (DSIT) AI Adoption in UK Businesses survey 2023</a></span></p></div><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">68%</span><p class="text-text-muted">Share of marketers globally who said AI significantly changed their SEO and content strategy in 2024, per Semrush State of Content Marketing report. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://www.semrush.com/blog/content-marketing-statistics/" class="text-teal hover:underline">Semrush State of Content Marketing 2024</a></span></p></div><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">£900 billion</span><p class="text-text-muted">Estimated potential contribution of AI to the UK economy by 2030, per PwC UK. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://www.pwc.co.uk/economic-services/assets/macroeconomic-impact-of-ai-technical-report-feb-18.pdf" class="text-teal hover:underline">PwC UK AI Impact Index</a></span></p></div><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">34%</span><p class="text-text-muted">Share of UK CMOs who cited AI-driven search as a top-three priority for 2025, per Gartner CMO Spend Survey. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://www.gartner.com/en/marketing/research/cmo-spend-survey" class="text-teal hover:underline">Gartner CMO Spend and Strategy Survey 2024</a></span></p></div><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">45%</span><p class="text-text-muted">Share of UK organisations that increased investment in AI tools and capabilities in 2024. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://www.mckinsey.com/capabilities/quantumblack/our-insights/the-state-of-ai" class="text-teal hover:underline">McKinsey Global Survey on AI 2024</a></span></p></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Citation and Visibility Trends in AI-Generated Responses</h2><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">40%</span><p class="text-text-muted">Estimated average click-through rate reduction on organic results when Google AI Overviews are present, based on early testing data reported by Semrush. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://www.semrush.com/blog/google-ai-overviews/" class="text-teal hover:underline">Semrush Blog: Google AI Overviews Impact Study</a></span></p></div><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">Top 10</span><p class="text-text-muted">Google AI Overviews predominantly cite sources that rank in the top 10 organic results for the same query, reinforcing the link between traditional SEO authority and AI citation. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://www.semrush.com/blog/google-ai-overviews/" class="text-teal hover:underline">Semrush Blog: Google AI Overviews Study</a></span></p></div><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">70%</span><p class="text-text-muted">Share of AI Overview citations that come from sources already appearing on page one of standard Google results, per Semrush analysis. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://www.semrush.com/blog/google-ai-overviews/" class="text-teal hover:underline">Semrush</a></span></p></div><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">9%</span><p class="text-text-muted">Average organic traffic decline observed on pages where AI Overviews appeared for target queries, based on early Ahrefs case study data. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/google-ai-overviews/" class="text-teal hover:underline">Ahrefs Blog</a></span></p></div><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">£635 million</span><p class="text-text-muted">UK search advertising spend attributed to Google in 2023, underlining the financial stakes of search visibility shifts. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://www.statista.com/statistics/309866/google-uk-advertising-revenue/" class="text-teal hover:underline">Statista UK Digital Advertising</a></span></p></div><div class="flex items-start gap-4 border-b border-border pb-4 mb-4"><span class="text-3xl font-bold text-teal flex-shrink-0">3x</span><p class="text-text-muted">Brands with structured data markup and E-E-A-T signals are cited in AI Overviews at approximately three times the rate of those without, per Semrush structured data research. <span class="text-text-muted text-xs">Source: <a href="https://www.semrush.com/blog/google-ai-overviews/" class="text-teal hover:underline">Semrush</a></span></p></div>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto my-8"><table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse"><caption class="text-left font-semibold mb-2 text-teal">AI Search Platforms: UK Relevance and Citation Index, Q2 2026</caption><thead class="bg-off-white"><tr><th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold text-teal border-b border-border">Platform</th><th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold text-teal border-b border-border">UK-Relevant Monthly Users (Latest Available)</th><th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold text-teal border-b border-border">Primary Web Index / Data Source</th><th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold text-teal border-b border-border">AI Overview / Answer Format</th><th class="px-3 py-2 text-left font-semibold text-teal border-b border-border">Primary Public Source</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Google AI Overviews</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">1 billion+ globally (May 2024 milestone); UK share proportional to 92.7% Google UK search share</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Google Search index</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Inline AI-generated summaries above organic results</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Google I/O 2024: https://blog.google/technology/ai/google-io-2024-keynote/</td></tr><tr><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">ChatGPT (with Browse)</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">200 million+ weekly active users globally (Aug 2024); Browse mode powered by Bing index</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Bing / OpenAI proprietary training data</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Conversational answers with inline citations when Browse enabled</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">OpenAI: https://openai.com/blog/chatgpt-can-now-see-hear-and-speak</td></tr><tr><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Microsoft Copilot</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Integrated into Windows 11 (installed on 31% of UK PCs per Statcounter); Bing market share 3.9% UK</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Bing index</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Cited conversational answers; deep Microsoft 365 integration</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Statcounter: https://gs.statcounter.com/search-engine-market-share/all/united-kingdom</td></tr><tr><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Perplexity AI</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">100 million+ monthly active users globally (Jan 2025); 2.3 million estimated UK monthly visits (Similarweb Q4 2024)</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Bing + proprietary web crawl</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Cited answers with numbered source references</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Reuters: https://www.reuters.com/technology/artificial-intelligence/perplexity-ai-valued-9-billion-new-funding-round-2025-01-07/</td></tr><tr><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Google Gemini</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Integrated into Google Search and Workspace; UK Google search share 92.7%</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Google Search index + proprietary training</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Conversational and multimodal answers; replacing Bard</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Google Blog: https://blog.google/technology/ai/bard-gemini-advanced-app/</td></tr><tr><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Claude (Anthropic)</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">No UK-specific monthly user figure publicly disclosed; growing enterprise adoption in UK</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Anthropic proprietary training data; no live web index by default</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Conversational answers; citations limited to uploaded documents unless web tool enabled</td><td class="px-3 py-2 border-b border-border text-sm text-text-muted">Anthropic: https://www.anthropic.com/claude</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

      <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      {faqs.map((f) => (
        <div class="mb-6">
          <p class="font-semibold text-teal mb-1">{f.q}</p>
          <p class="text-text-muted">{f.a}</p>
        </div>
      ))}

      <AuthorBox />
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
